{"event_id": "e7c22c1a-1be5-4da9-8f22-f75f0e7fe215", "trace_id": "eac925b26603409e", "session_id": "ee4eac78", "timestamp": "2026-05-05T06:25:47.139199+00:00", "tool": "filesystem.write_file", "args_hash": "50b2921d2e308909aa4359209dd39a4d6d86269b2b122c5ecb425c52c475bcbc", "args_redacted": {"path": "workspace/ai_safety_summary.txt", "content": "============================================================\nAI SAFETY RESEARCH — 3 MOST IMPORTANT RECENT FINDINGS\n============================================================\n\nDate: 2025\n\n1. CONSTITUTIONAL AI (Anthropic)\n   - Finding: Self-critique and self-revision methods reduce harmful\n     model outputs by approximately 40%.\n   - Significance: Instead of relying solely on human feedback (RLHF),\n     models are trained using a \"constitution\" of principles to\n     evaluate and revise their own responses. This makes AI systems\n     more transparently aligned and less dependent on costly human\n     annotation. It represents a scalable path toward safer AI\n     behavior without sacrificing helpfulness.\n\n2. MECHANISTIC INTERPRETABILITY — Transformer Circuits (MIT)\n   - Finding: Researchers can now identify and understand specific\n     circuits within transformer models, enabling targeted editing\n     of model behavior.\n   - Significance: By reverse-engineering how transformers process\n     information internally, researchers can locate and modify the\n     specific components responsible for undesirable behaviors\n     (e.g., bias, deception, or sycophancy). This moves safety from\n     a \"black box\" approach toward precise, engineering-level\n     control over model internals.\n\n3. SCALABLE OVERSIGHT — Debate Protocols (DeepMind)\n   - Finding: Structured debate protocols allow human judges to\n     effectively supervise tasks that exceed human capabilities.\n   - Significance: As AI systems become superhuman in more domains,\n     humans can no longer directly evaluate their outputs. Debate\n     protocols — where two AI agents argue opposing sides while a\n     human judges — provide a mechanism to maintain meaningful\n     human oversight even when AI surpasses human expertise. This\n     is a critical step toward safely deploying increasingly\n     capable systems.\n\n============================================================\n"}, "input_labels": {"SI": "SI:LOW", "DS": "DS:NORMAL"}, "policy_decision": "ALLOW", "matched_rule": "", "rule_reason": "No defense baseline — PEP bypassed", "prev_event_hash": "4c07b315ae56d850266e1357c1d708e408d3fc53935426562da0f927b843a8fa", "event_hash": "0589b284d1e4692fd83797733bee131797d04b09f5a7f0b03dc5fed46196cffa"}
